Step1:Select freestyle
Step2:Select Source code management and click git
Step3:Give repo url
Step4:Select any repo in github and take only https url as ssh will not support in jenkins
Step5:Its a public repo no need of credentials and select */master in branches to build section.
If it is private repo need to take token from git hub and add the token in credentials of jenkins.
To get the token go to developer settings---select Personal access token--Tokens(classic)---Generate new token(Classic) and select repo scope of first box and save.
Keep save the token to login the same repo
Step6:Save and buildnow
Step7:Build will fail as git not install
Step8:In server install git by using command
yum install git -y 
Step9:once again buildnow and it will pass the pipeline this time
Step10:check logs in pipeline and take path and check in server using cd path.Files can be seen
